{
  "texts": [
    "First using MF encodings as cues, we seek to retrieve either MF or PP encodings by respectively setting a high or low threshold.",
    "As we load the network with increasingly more stored examples, distinct MF examples can consistently be retrieved with high threshold (Fig. 3D).",
    "Meanwhile, retrieval of PP examples with low threshold fails above 1-2 examples stored per concept.",
    "At large example loads, the network again retrieves a sneaker memory when cued with sneaker examples.",
    "However, this memory is the same for all sneaker cues and appears similar to the average image over all sneaker examples (Fig. 2A), which captures common sneaker features (Supplementary Fig."
  ]
}